[![calderonFOTO](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2009/10/calderonFOTO-300x199.jpg)](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2009/10/calderonFOTO.JPG)

More than 14000 Costa Ricans who were away from TV sets today at 3pm were able
to view online the judgment of ex President Rafael Ángel Calderón when at
least 3 different websites decided to present the ruling via online streaming
services, a [record for the Costa Rican online
community](http://twitter.com/watchcr/status/4637751139). Not only was
streaming used, media also uploaded[ images through twitpic
](http://twitpic.com/kes8p)to be used [on
twitter](http://twitter.com/nacion/status/4638413246). All these are recent
developments as media starts to adapt to social networking tools for
journalism.

Through microblogging tool Twitter, using the tag[
#sentencia](http://twitter.com/#search?q=%23sentencia), [#cajafischel
](http://twitter.com/#search?q=%23cajafischel)or
[#Calderon](http://twitter.com/#search?q=%23calderon), viewers followed and
commented the ruling, where the ex President was convicted and will have to
serve to a [5 year prison sentence for corruption
charges](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/8291867.stm).

Presidential candidate Ottón Solis has already [uploaded a video commentary on
YouTube](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YfvedDok9RA) regarding the sentence.

Journalist Amelia Rueda also [tweeted the happenings
](http://twitter.com/ameliarueda)inside the tribunals. She[ posted a short
audio clip](http://twitter.com/ameliarueda/status/4636100060) where the
accused ex president spoke about[ his hopes regarding the
veredict](http://u.phoreo.com/37.mp3), which you can hear by clicking on the
player at the bottom of the post.

Journalist Cristian Cambronero posted an [entry on his
blog](http://www.fusildechispas.com/2009/10/calderon-culpable-se-esfumo-el-
sueno/#comments) where he refers to the ex president's now crushed intentions
of running once again for president, confident he would be declared innocent.
[Lucía comments](http://www.fusildechispas.com/2009/10/calderon-culpable-se-
esfumo-el-sueno/#comment-292930) in that post:

> El jalón de orejas no es solo para para Calderón y compañía (pobrecito
> nada¡¡¡¡ si no quiere ir a la cárcel no sea corrupto, así de simple), es
> para la clase política en general, que aquí como en otros países creen que
> uno está para serviles y no ellos para servir …  
>  Más valioso que el dinero que tienen devolver (no se cuanto es) es el haber
> recuperado cierta confianza en el sistema político, y como dice un conocido
> anuncio de tarjetas de crédito, eso no tiene precio…

This slap on the hand is not only for Calderon and company (poor guy nothing!!
If he doesn't want to go to jail, then don't be corrupt, it's that simple), is
for the political class in general, who believe here as in other countries
that everyone should serve them and not that they have to serve…

